Source: pg-strict
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/spa5k/pg_strict

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-strict
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-strict
Depends: postgresql-PGVERSION, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Prevent dangerous UPDATE and DELETE without WHERE clause
  pg_strict is a PostgreSQL extension that prevents dangerous UPDATE and DELETE
  statements by requiring a WHERE clause.
